Stress-test E3: Point record-field commutativity.

Cryptol property (inline Point type in driver):
    \(p1 p2 : Point) -> point_add p1 p2 == point_add p2 p1
where Point = { x : [32], y : [32] }.

Exercises RecordType.rec reduction on a two-field record and
bvAdd_comm applied per field. The emitted goal has ~80 lines
of RecordType.rec projections; after `obtain ⟨x, y⟩ := p` these
reduce to `.1`/`.2` accesses. Four tactic lines (intro +
obtain×2 + rw×2 + simp).

Finding: `obtain` destructures through nested `RecordType`
cleanly, and `simp [bvEq_refl]` collapses the final ite chain.
No support-library changes required.
